KW  - Safe assets
KW  - Private money
KW  - Repo
KW  - Monetary policy
KW  - Federal Reserve
AB  - The existing literature has shown that an increase in the demand for safe assets induces the private sector to create more of them. Focusing on repos backed by US Treasuries, I theoretically and empirically show that an increase in the demand for safe assets leads to a decrease in repos outstanding. Because Treasuries are safe assets, an increase in the demand for safe assets compresses their term premia, reducing incentives to issue repos. Thus, the sensitivity of private safe asset creation depends on whether the collateral backing them are safe assets themselves. The sensitivity of the Federal Reserve’s reverse repurchase agreement (RRP) operations has the same sign as existing studies.
